cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless networks and their energy allocation policy, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes a utility-based approach to energy allocation, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the allocation of renewable energy in cellular networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper formulates an optimization problem for energy allocation, which falls under the scope of computational engineering. 
5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The paper deals with the use of renewable energy in cellular networks, which can be seen as an emerging technology in the field of computer science.
